title: Eliminates statutory authority of social services official to receive and dispose of a deed, mortgage, or lien; repealer
summary: Eliminates statutory authority of social services official to receive and dispose of a deed, mortgage, or lien.
actClause: AN ACT to amend the social services law and the abandoned property law, in relation to powers of social services officials to receive and dispose of certain property and to repeal section 106 of the social services law, relating to powers of social services official to receive and dispose of a deed, mortgage, or lien
